properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant rainfall expected Wednesday night through Thursday. A developing low pressure system will track over Northeastern Ontario on Thursday. Rain ahead of this system is expected to develop Wednesday night and continue Thursday before tapering to scattered showers Friday. Total rainfall amounts of 30 to 50 mm are possible with the heaviest rain falling Thursday during the day. The ground, already near saturation, has little ability to absorb further rainfall. Localized flooding in low-lying areas is possible. For information concerning flooding, please consult your local conservation authority or Ontario Ministry of Natural Resources and Forestry District Office. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.
Expires: 2019-05-08T06:28:57-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2019-05-07T22:29:57-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.1168857071.2019
Area: West Nipissing - French River, North Bay - Powassan - Mattawa, Espanola - Killarney, Manitoulin Island
properties.Author: Environment Canada

properties.Title: Precautionary Drinking Water Advisory For Danielson Provincial Park
properties.Summary:
Description: A Precautionary Drinking Water Advisory has been issued for Danielson Provincial Park as part of the seasonal start up of the waterworks. This advisory is for any individuals who may access water from the park distribution system. This advisory is in effect until testing results confirm the water safe.

properties.Title: Update: Flood Warning Continues For The Red River From Emerson To The Red River Floodway Channel Inlet
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre continues to issue a Flood Warning on the Red River from Emerson to the Red River Floodway channel inlet due to high water flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions given by local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2019-05-08T11:00:00-05:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2019-05-07T11:54:54-05:00, 3CB826B2-92F4-A74E-683F-5E51DEF4CACD
Area: Red River from Emerson to the Red River Floodway channel inlet
properties.Author: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Frost may damage some crops in frost-prone areas. Temperatures will drop slightly below the freezing mark overnight tonight. There will be ground frost over several areas the following night as well. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain is expected or occurring. A warm front passing over the northern Mackenzie River on Wednesday morning will likely bring a few hours of freezing rain to the area. Freezing rain will change over to rain later in the afternoon when temperatures warm to above freezing. ### Surfaces such as highways, roads, walkways and parking lots may become icy and slippery. Freezing rain warnings are issued when rain falling in sub-zero temperatures creates ice build-up and icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NTStorm.
Expires: 2019-05-08T13:12:16-00:00
